claim.claim-text:
A combined system comprising intercooled recuperative gas turbine (ICR GT) and supercritical refrigerant Rankine cycle (RRC)/ vapor compression refrigeration cycle (VCRC);

the ICR GT includes:
a compressor with several compression parts separated by multiple intercoolers (10);
a combustor or heater to heat up the compressed gas with fuel burning or heat transfer;
a turbine with several stages to generate output power;
several intercoolers to cool the compressed air by refrigerant working fluid;
a main recuperator (11) to heat up compressed air before entering combustor/heater;
and

several cooling air recuperators to heat up cooling air from compressor before cooling turbine stages;

the supercritical RRC includes:
supercritical refrigerant fluid-flue gas heat exchangers (12&2) to preheat and heat up supercritical refrigerant fluid above critical temperature;
one or several refrigerant fluid turbines (3) to generate output power via refrigerant fluid expansion;
a refrigerant fluid condenser (4) to condense gaseous fluid into liquid state or cool supercritical refrigerant;
pressure pump (5) to pressurize refrigerant fluid above the critical pressure; and
an optional refrigerant recuperator to recover waste heat from the discharge of refrigerant turbine;
the VCRC includes:
gas turbine (GT) inlet air cooler (9) to increase air density;
refrigerant fluid internal heat exchanger (8) to adjust intercooler refrigerant coolant temperature;
throttle valves or expanders (6&13) to reduce refrigerant fluid temperature; and
refrigerant fluid compressors (14&7) to pressurize refrigerant steam to the condenser shared with refrigerant Rankine cycle;
the refrigerant-gas heater (2) receives flue gas from the main recuperator (11) of the intercooled recuperative gas turbine, it supplies heated fluid to refrigerant fluid turbine (3), which discharges expanded refrigerant to condenser (4) where the refrigerant is cooled/condensed before supplied to pressure pump (5), then these pumps pressurize supercritical refrigerant to the intercoolers (10) and refrigerant fluid preheater (12) for preheating, finally the preheated refrigerant is supplied to refrigerant-gas heater (2) to be heated above the critical temperature;

the throttle valves or expanders (6&13) receive refrigerant from condenser (4), they also supply cooled refrigerant to inlet air cooler (9) where the refrigerant absorbs the heat of inlet air and gets vaporized; the vaporized refrigerant goes through the first compressor (7) and the second compressor (14) before arriving to condenser (4); throttle valve or expander (6) also supplies cooled refrigerant to refrigerant internal heat exchanger (8) where the refrigerant coolant to intercoolers (10) is cooled by vaporizing the cooled refrigerant, the vaporized refrigerant is then directed to the first compressor (7) before discharged to the condenser (4).
